In the Sarum Missal the Chants of seven Kyries are given, and the full words, or the Verses, of nine Kyries are to be found at the end of the Missal: six of these are in the York List. The Hereford Missal has sixteen, including all those given or referred to in the other Uses, and five peculiar to itself.
